com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.typedec
Interface NativeBehaviorSignature

All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeConstructorSignature, NativeFieldMethodSignature, NativeInstanceFieldMethodSignature, NativeInstanceMethodSignature, NativeMethodSignature, NativeStaticFieldMethodSignature, NativeStaticMethodSignature
public interface NativeBehaviorSignature

The NativeBehaviorSignature interface represents the native signature declaration of all method types.

Describes how a method must be called using a native call. The parameters and return type are declared using native variable types, and the native container of the method is declared with a native class (needed if instance or constructor).

Method and parameter names are not needed, as a matter of fact a signature may be declared without a real concrete Java method supporting it (with the exception of constructors).

Signatures are declared using NativeSignatureManager methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

getSignatureString

java.lang.String getSignatureString(java.lang.String name)
Returns a string representation of the native signature using the specified method/field name.

This method is useful to view how is registered a native method instance in a DLL using DynamicLibrary.addDLLBehavior(String,NativeBehaviorSignature) or JNIEasyLibrary.exportBehavior(String,NativeBehavior)

The returned string follows the following format:

  • Constructor:
    ClassName.(ParamsDec)
  • Static method:
    name(ParamsDec)
  • Instance method:
    ClassName.name(ParamsDec)
  • Static field-method:
    name(int,FieldDec)
  • Instance field-method:
    ClassName.name(int,VarTypeNativeOfField)
Where ParamsDec format is the same of getDeclarationString(), and VarTypeNativeOfField is the variable native type of the field with format explained in NativeVarTypeManager.dec(String,String[]).

Parameters:
name - the used method/field name to construct the string.
Returns:
the string representation of the native signature.
See Also:
DynamicLibrary.findBehaviorBySignature(String)

newBehaviorReflection

NativeBehaviorReflection newBehaviorReflection(java.lang.reflect.Member member)
Creates a native behavior reflection instance using this signature and the specified java.lang.reflect.Member object.

The reflection object (Field, Method or Constructor) describing a Java method/field, must be compatible with the native signature, the container class of the method/field (if defined) and parameters must be the same, otherwise an exception is thrown.

This behavior signature defines the native behavior missing in the reflection object.

The ReturnedReflection returned holds the submitted reflection object.

Parameters:
member - the reflection object.
Returns:
a new NativeBehaviorReflection as a callback of the constructor defined in the native signature.
See Also:
newDirectCallback(Member), TypeCanBeNativeCapable.wrapValue(Object)

newDirectCallback

NativeDirectCallback newDirectCallback(java.lang.reflect.Member member)
Creates a new direct callback object of the method defined using the specified java.lang.reflect.Member object.

The reflection object (Field, Method or Constructor) describing a Java method, must be compatible with the native signature, the container class of the method (if defined) and parameters must be the same, otherwise an exception is thrown.

This behavior signature defines the native behavior missing in the reflection object.

A new Java class is created "on the fly" and loaded on memory using the current ClassLoader. This object works like NativeBehaviorReflection, exporting a normal Java method as native, but the managed Java method (the method described in member), is called not using reflection. The new Java class has a name constructed using the Member object info, only the first direct callback using a Member object creates and loads a new class, a second instance uses the loaded class and is created without reflection.

If the current ClassLoader is not an enhancer ClassLoader, the method ClassLoader.defineClass(String,byte[],int,int) is called using reflection (because this method is protected) previously enabling private/protected calls with Method.setAccessible(true), a SecurityException is raised if disabling the access checking is forbidden.

Parameters:
member - the reflection object.
Returns:
a new NativeDirectCallback as a callback of the specified method with member.
See Also:
newBehaviorReflection(Member), NativeTypeManager.getClassLoader()

attachBehavior

NativeBehavior attachBehavior(NativeAddress address,
                              long offset)
Creates and attachs to the specified address and offset of a native method a native instance of a predefined class implementing the interface NativeBehavior With this object the native method can be called from Java using this signature.

Depending on this signature type, the returned method may be a NativeConstructor NativeStaticMethod, NativeInstanceMethod, NativeStaticFieldMethod, NativeInstanceFieldMethod,

Parameters:
address - the main address of the native method
offset - the relative offset of the the main address
Returns:
the native instance mapping the specified native method with this signature.
